      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "## Calendar date indicators are clearer\n\nThis update makes it easier to tell **today** apart from the **daily note you currently have open**.\n\n### What's improved\n\n- Today is shown with an accent-colored outline in the calendar.\n- The open daily note is shown with a filled accent background.\n- If today and the open note are the same day, both signals stay visible.\n- The list view now follows the same pattern as the calendar grid.\n- Right-click color tags in the list view keep their highlight on hover and active rows, with no change needed from you.\n\nNo settings changes are required.\n\n**Full changelog:** https://github.com/xRyul/calendar-for-daily-notes/compare/2.1.5...2.1.6\n",
